---
// Standard DXP Component - Control Group A
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Control Group A - Standard DXP Components"
  description="Standard DXP components without AI optimization - baseline implementation for comparison"
  group="A"
>
  <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
    <h2>Standard DXP Components</h2>
    <p>
      This page represents the <strong>control group</strong> using standard DXP 
      (Digital Experience Platform) components without AI optimization.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Purpose</h3>
    <p>
      Serves as the baseline implementation for comparison against GAIO-optimized 
      components in Test Group B.
    </p>

    <h3>Key Characteristics</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Basic HTML structure using <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> elements</li>
      <li>Standard metadata tags only</li>
      <li>No JSON-LD structured data</li>
      <li>Traditional SEO approach</li>
      <li>No semantic HTML5 elements</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What We're Testing</h3>
    <p>
      This control group helps us measure the baseline performance metrics:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Organic search rankings</li>
      <li>Search result click-through rates</li>
      <li>User engagement (time on page, bounce rate)</li>
      <li>Accessibility scores</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem; padding: 1rem; background: #f0f0f0; border-left: 4px solid #0066cc;">
      <strong>Note:</strong> Compare this implementation with 
      <a href="/test-group-b" style="color: #0066cc;">Test Group B</a> 
      to see the GAIO optimization differences.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

